President Donald J. Trump has declared a major disaster in the State of Iowa due to severe storms, tornadoes, straight-line winds, and flooding that occurred from July 19 to July 23, 2017. This declaration allows for federal assistance to supplement state, tribal, and local recovery efforts. Federal funding will be available on a cost-sharing basis for emergency work, repair or replacement of damaged facilities, and hazard mitigation measures. Michael L. Parker has been named as the Federal Coordinating Officer for federal recovery operations in the affected areas. Further designations may be made in the future based on damage assessments. For more information, contact the FEMA News Desk.